modules.description: This module implements asynchronous operations for interacting with Azure Blob Storage, providing functions to sign requests, upload, download, append to, and delete blobs. It works with HTTP methods, headers, and URIs via the Cohttp library, along with connection configurations from Azblob.Conn and SSL settings from Conduit_async. Concrete use cases include streaming file uploads, appending log data to existing blobs, and managing blob storage objects with async I/O in a distributed system.
